msgid "Painting Animation Levels"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/painting_animation_levels.rst:5
msgid ""
"Toonz animation levels, both those cleaned up, and those made directly in"
" Toonz, can be painted by using the styles stored in the palette and a "
"set of tools."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/painting_animation_levels.rst:7
msgid ""
"All Toonz drawings are made of outlines, determined by the lines of "
"scanned drawings or vectors of vector drawings, and areas defined by "
"outlines. Lines and vectors can be painted or erased, partially or for "
"their full extent; areas can be filled with styles, or remain empty, with"
" complete transparency."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/painting_animation_levels.rst:9
msgid ""
"All the painting work is not saved until you save the related level, or "
"the scene (see  :ref:`Saving Levels <saving_levels>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/painting_animation_levels.rst:11
msgid ""
"If the computer performance worsens during the painting process of raster"
" animation levels, try activating the Minimize Raster Image Fragmentation"
" option in the Preferences > General dialog (see  :ref:`Optimizing the "
"Memory Usage <optimizing_the_memory_usage>`  )."
msgstr ""

